excerpt: Eccentric Art Nouveau-style setting for private Victorian art collection and temporary exhibitions.
detail_description: The Russell Cotes Art Gallery & Museum is a captivating historic house located in Bournemouth, England. Built by Merton Russell-Cotes as a birthday gift for his wife Annie in 1901, this extravagant Art Nouveau-style villa overlooks the sea and showcases the couple's love for art, travel, world cultures, and natural history. The museum features an impressive collection of British art, along with oriental souvenirs gathered from around the globe by the Russell-Cotes family.
name: Russell Cotes Art Gallery & Museum
address: Russell-Cotes Art Gallery & Museum East, W Cliff Promenade, Bournemouth BH1 3AA, United Kingdom

excerpt: Explore marine ecosystems at a waterside aquarium, plus feeding sessions and an underwater tunnel.
detail_description: The Oceanarium, situated on Bournemouth Pier, is a captivating aquarium that provides an educational and entertaining experience for visitors. It offers a variety of activities such as feeding sessions with reef sharks, stingrays, turtles, otters, and penguins. The aquarium showcases diverse marine species including Nemo's friends - the clownfish, sharks, crocodiles, reptiles, and seahorses.
name: Oceanarium
address: Bournemouth, BH2 5AA, United Kingdom

excerpt: Victorian pier with an amusement arcade, a variety theatre, a cafe and boat trips along the coast.
detail_description: Bournemouth Pier, originally built in 1856 as a small jetty, has evolved into a Victorian pier featuring an amusement arcade, a variety theatre, and a cafe. Spanning over 1000ft long, it has been rebuilt multiple times due to storms and wartime precautions. Positioned at the heart of Bournemouth's beach, the pier serves as a starting point for seaside walks and offers various shops and attractions along its length.
name: Bournemouth Pier
address: Pier Approach, Bournemouth, BH2 5AA, United Kingdom

excerpt: Touring operas, shows, comedians and ballets perform on the stage of this venue in a 1920s pavilion.
detail_description: The Bournemouth Pavilion Theatre, housed in a 1920s pavilion with original Art Deco design, offers a nostalgic yet captivating entertainment experience. Situated in the south end of Bournemouth Lower Gardens, this Grade II listed building is known for its vintage charm and state-of-the-art facilities. Hosting a diverse array of events including musicals, opera, ballet, pantomime, comedy shows and fashion events throughout the year.
name: Bournemouth Pavilion Theatre
address: Westover Rd, Bournemouth, BH1 2BU, United Kingdom

excerpt: A chance to sit in the cockpits of vintage planes including a Spitfire, plus flight simulator.
detail_description: The Bournemouth Aviation Museum, located near Bournemouth Airport, is a must-visit for aviation enthusiasts. The museum boasts an impressive collection of civil and military aircraft, as well as other exhibits like the Control Tower and Airport Fire Engine. Visitors can immerse themselves in a hands-on experience by sitting in the cockpits of various iconic planes such as the Spitfire and Boeing 737.
name: Bournemouth Aviation Museum
address: B3073 Merritown Ln, Christchurch, BH23 6BA, United Kingdom

detail_description: Hengistbury Head is a nature reserve located in Poole and Bournemouth, offering diverse habitats such as heathland, grassland, scrub, forest, wetlands, and coastland. It also boasts internationally significant archaeology and geology. Visitors can take a land train to Mudeford Sandspit for a relaxing ride and enjoy refreshments at the on-site cafes while taking in the view.
name: Hengistbury Head
address: Unnamed Rd, Bournemouth BH6 4EN, UK, United Kingdom

excerpt: Bournemouth is a coastal resort town in the Bournemouth, Christchurch and Poole unitary authority area, in the ceremonial county of Dorset, England. At the 2021 census, the built-up area had a population of 196,455, making it the largest town in Dorset. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Bournemouth, located in Dorset, England, is a coastal resort town known for its warm and swimmable beach that stretches for seven miles. The lively Victorian pier offers arcade games and bars, while pastel beach huts and a charming promenade complete the classic British seaside scene. Established in 1812 as a health resort, Bournemouth has evolved into a vibrant town with two universities and the Bournemouth International Centre (BIC), hosting world-class music acts.
name: Bournemouth
address: United Kingdom

excerpt: Upmarket Westbourne has a thriving shopping district, with independent fashion boutiques, thrift stores, cafes, and pubs on Poole and Seamoor roads, which are linked by a Victorian covered arcade. It’s also popular for quiet strolls, thanks to its chines – dry, wooded gorges that run to the sandy beach, passing clifftop green spaces like Argyll Gardens. Alum Chine is spanned by a quaint suspension bridge.
detail_description: Westbourne is a charming and upscale neighborhood known for its thriving shopping district. The area boasts independent fashion boutiques, thrift stores, cafes, and pubs connected by a Victorian covered arcade on Poole and Seamoor roads. It's also popular for leisurely strolls, with dry wooded gorges called chines that lead to the sandy beach, passing through clifftop green spaces like Argyll Gardens. Alum Chine features a quaint suspension bridge adding to its allure.
name: Westbourne
address: Bournemouth, UK

excerpt: Restored Victorian pier, with lamps, kiosks and wooden boarding, hosting art exhibitions and events.
detail_description: Boscombe Pier is a beautifully restored Victorian pier that offers a variety of attractions and activities. It hosts art exhibitions and events, making it a cultural hub in the area. The surrounding area includes Christchurch Harbour, Mudeford Sandbank, Hengistbury Head, Southbourne Beach, and Fishermans Walk. Visitors can enjoy free beach activities such as swimming, sunbathing, and beach volleyball.
name: Boscombe Pier
address: 2494 Undercliff Dr, Boscombe, Bournemouth BH5 1BN, United Kingdom

excerpt: Private garden founded in 1920 with visits, an on-site tea room & retail sales of plants & gifts.
detail_description: Compton Acres is a renowned private garden established in 1920, located in the Canford Cliffs area of Poole, Dorset. It encompasses seven distinct gardens with international themes, including a striking Japanese garden featuring impressive koi carp. The Italian garden boasts formal elegance with fountains and statues, while the rock and water garden showcases over 300 plant species.
name: Compton Acres
address: Canford Cliffs Rd, Poole, BH13 7ES, UK

excerpt: Waterpark and leisure centre featuring multiple rides and flumes for kids, plus a water play area.
detail_description: Splashdown, located in Poole's Tower Park complex, is a premier waterpark offering a thrilling experience for visitors of all ages. With 13 exhilarating indoor and outdoor flume rides, as well as 3 splash zones for young children, there's something for everyone. From the high-speed drop of Infinity to the rapid descent down the Screamer, there are rides tailored to different levels of bravery and group sizes.

address: Tower Pk, Poole, BH12 4NY, United Kingdom

excerpt: Sandy stretch with amusement arcades on 2 piers & backed by cliffside gardens & terrace restaurants.
detail_description: Bournemouth Beach is the main beach in town, featuring a sandy stretch of coastline with two piers and cliffside gardens. The Bournemouth Pier offers various indoor and outdoor activities for families, including the Oceanarium and RockReef climbing walls. The beach itself boasts spacious golden sands, awarded the Blue Flag for safety and cleanliness. It is also known as one of the safest beaches in the UK, with RNLI Lifeguards stationed there from April to September.

address: Undercliff Rd, Bournemouth, BH1 3NZ, United Kingdom

The course is designed for all ages, making it perfect for families, couples, or groups of friends. As you navigate through rocks, runs, and gravestones, you'll be immersed in the world of smugglers and their daring escapades. The scenic coastal views add to the excitement as you compete to see who has the skills to conquer the course.
name: Smugglers Cove Adventure Golf
address: Pier Approach, Bournemouth, BH2 5AA, United Kingdom

detail_description: The International Centre is a versatile event venue located in the heart of a bustling city. It offers state-of-the-art facilities and flexible spaces suitable for various events such as conferences, trade shows, concerts, and corporate functions. The centre boasts modern amenities and professional staff to ensure seamless event execution. With its convenient location and well-equipped spaces, the International Centre is an ideal choice for hosting diverse gatherings with ease and style.
name: International Centre
address: Exeter Rd, Bournemouth, BH2 5BH, UK

excerpt: Leafy green space featuring attractions such as mini-golf & a giant tethered balloon, plus events.
detail_description: Bournemouth Parks - Lower Gardens is a beautifully maintained Victorian-designed green space just a few minutes' walk from the shoreline. It features gorgeous floral displays, an aviary, mini-golf course, and a large rock garden. The park also hosts regular live music performances at the bandstand and seasonal events such as open-air art exhibitions in summer and Christmas Tree Wonderland in winter. Visitors can enjoy picnics amidst plenty of green space.
name: Bournemouth Parks - Lower Gardens
address: Westover Road, Bournemouth, BH2 5AH, United Kingdom

excerpt: Beachfront gardens with bright flower beds, paths, a playground, cafe & 18-hole mini golf course.
detail_description: Boscombe Chine Gardens is a picturesque beachfront attraction featuring vibrant flower beds, winding paths, a playground, and an 18-hole mini golf course. Nestled near the shores of Boscombe Bay, this two-mile-long gorge offers towering cliffs and a riverside path. Maintained by a local conservancy group, the gardens provide various recreational opportunities such as walking trails, an underground tunnel to explore, and an elevator offering river views from below.
name: Boscombe Chine Gardens
address: Sea Rd, Boscombe, Bournemouth, BH5 1BL, United Kingdom

excerpt: Hiking, picnics & wildlife viewing, especially of red squirrels, are popular at this historic spot.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Poole Harbour, Brownsea Island is a captivating destination that seamlessly blends history with natural beauty. This National Trust gem is renowned for its rich wildlife, particularly the charming red squirrels that scamper through its lush landscapes. Visitors can embark on scenic hikes or enjoy delightful picnics while soaking in breathtaking views of the Purbeck Hills.
name: Brownsea Island
address: United Kingdom

excerpt: Gothic revival mansion dating from 1836, with restored exteriors, plus tearoom and gardens.
detail_description: Highcliffe Castle, a Gothic revival mansion built in the 1830s, showcases restored exteriors and offers visitors a tearoom and gardens to explore. The Grade listed cliff top mansion is an excellent example of Romantic and Picturesque architecture from the late 18th and early 19th centuries. Despite its relatively young age, the castle's medieval French masonry gives it an older appearance, complemented by its Gothic revival features and ancient stained glass.
name: Highcliffe Castle
address: Rothesay Dr, Highcliffe, Christchurch BH23 4LE, United Kingdom

excerpt: Amusement park with themed rides, inflatable slide, runaway train and trampolines, plus events.
detail_description: Adventure Wonderland is a beloved theme park near Bournemouth Airport, catering to children under 11. The park features over 30 rides and attractions, including the Flying Elephants, Curvy Caterpillars Ride, and Mr Rabbits Big Bouncy Burrows. Families can also enjoy an indoor soft play center and entertainment at the Happydrome Theatre.
name: Adventure Wonderland
address: Merritown Ln, Hurn, Christchurch BH23 6BA, United Kingdom

detail_description: The Bournemouth Observation Wheel is a must-visit attraction in Bournemouth, offering stunning panoramic views of the beach, seafront, pier, Pavilion Theatre, and Lower Gardens. Standing at over 100 feet tall, this iconic Ferris wheel provides uninterrupted vistas of the town and coastline. Visitors can choose to ride during the day for breathtaking natural scenery or opt for a sunset or night-time experience to witness the warm glow of both natural and artificial light along the seafront.
name: Bournemouth Observation Wheel
address: Pier Approach, Bournemouth, BH2 5AA, United Kingdom

excerpt: Imposing Gothic Revival church with a landmark spire & the graves of Mary & Percy Bysshe Shelley.
detail_description: St Peter's Church in Bournemouth is a Gothic Revival masterpiece and an iconic landmark in the city. Built between 1844 and 1879, it is the oldest Church of England parish in the area and is listed as a Grade I building. Designed by architect G.E Street, this church boasts a rich Gothic Revival interior with stunning stained glass windows and unique wall paintings.
name: St Peter's Church
address: Hinton Rd, Bournemouth, BH1 2EE, United Kingdom

excerpt: Versatile conference and entertainment venue with 4 halls, staging music, comedy and dance shows.
detail_description: Nestled along the stunning south coast, the Bournemouth International Centre (BIC) stands out as a premier venue for both conferences and entertainment. With an impressive capacity of up to 10,000 guests, it features four versatile halls that cater to a diverse range of events including concerts, comedy shows, exhibitions, and even sports activities. The BIC is not just about large-scale gatherings; it also plays host to the annual Bournemouth Arts by the Sea Festival each October.
name: Bournemouth International Centre
address: International Centre, Exeter Rd, Bournemouth, BH2 5BH, United Kingdom

detail_description: The West Cliff Lift, also known as the West Cliff Funicular Railway, is a historic and charming mode of transportation in Bournemouth. This funicular railway offers a unique and scenic experience, providing easy access between the beach and clifftop with stunning coastal views along the way. Operating from Easter to the end of October, it's a convenient way to explore Bournemouth's beautiful coastline.
name: West Cliff Lift
address: W Cliff Promenade, Bournemouth, BH2 5DU, United Kingdom

excerpt: Natural history museum in a Victorian building, with fossils, minerals and an Egyptology collection.
detail_description: The Bournemouth Natural Science Society & Museum, housed in a captivating Victorian-era building, is a must-visit cultural attraction. It boasts an extensive collection of fossils, minerals, Egyptology artifacts, and diverse scientific items. The museum hosts various events including lectures, exhibitions, and field meetings. Visitors can immerse themselves in exhibits covering botany, wildlife, earth sciences, and dinosaur fossils. Educational areas offer opportunities to enhance understanding of biology, geology, and zoology.
name: Bournemouth Natural Science Society
address: 39 Christchurch Rd, Bournemouth, BH1 3NS, United Kingdom

excerpt: Museum outlining 2000 years of local history housed in a converted Victorian warehouse.
detail_description: Poole Museum, located in a converted Victorian warehouse on 4 High Street, Dorset, England, offers a comprehensive overview of the area's history spanning over 2000 years. The museum showcases various exhibits such as the Studland Bay Wreck and details about the Roman occupation and trade connections with Newfoundland. It also features artifacts like a 295 BC log boat found in Poole Harbour. Additionally, visitors can explore the town's maritime significance from ancient times to the present day.
name: Poole Museum
address: 4 High St, Poole, BH15 1BW, United Kingdom

excerpt: Complex featuring a rock-climbing wall, ropes course, zip line & cave-themed tunnels with ball pits.
detail_description: RockReef - Indoor Climbing Attraction is a thrilling adventure complex located at the end of Bournemouth Pier. It offers a variety of exciting activities such as rock climbing walls, ropes course, zip line, and cave-themed tunnels with ball pits. The attraction features 28 Clip n Climb themed indoor climbing walls that provide different levels of challenges for visitors.
name: RockReef - Indoor Climbing Attraction
address: Bournemouth Pier, Bournemouth, BH2 5AA, United Kingdom

excerpt: Poole is a coastal town in Dorset, southern England, known for its large natural harbour and sandy beaches. The Old Town has Georgian houses and Poole Museum, which explores local history in 4 buildings, including medieval Scaplen’s Court. From Poole Harbour, boats head south to Brownsea Island. This wooded area has trails and wildlife such as red squirrels, plus 16th-century Brownsea Castle, now a private hotel.
detail_description: Poole, a charming coastal town in southern England, is famous for its expansive natural harbor and beautiful sandy beaches. The Old Town area boasts elegant Georgian houses and the fascinating Poole Museum, spread across four historic buildings including the medieval Scaplen’s Court. Visitors can embark on boat trips from Poole Harbour to explore the scenic Brownsea Island, renowned for its lush woodlands, nature trails, and diverse wildlife like red squirrels.
name: Poole
address: United Kingdom

detail_description: Poole Harbour, Europe's largest natural harbor and the second biggest in the world after Sydney, is a haven for wildlife and water sports enthusiasts. The shallow waters of Holes Bay to the north are part of this internationally important RAMSAR site, attracting various bird species like Common Shelduck, Avocet, Black-tailed Godwit, Eurasian Spoonbill, and more.
name: Poole Harbour
address: United Kingdom

excerpt: Family centre for skiiing & snowboarding, with an adventure park, bistro & children's activities.
detail_description: Snowtrax Alpine Activity Centre & Snowsports Shop is a family-friendly destination in Christchurch that offers a wide range of activities for all ages. From skiing and snowboarding to mountain biking, white water rafting, and hiking, there's something for everyone. The centre also features an Alpine Adventure Park with various attractions for children, including forts, slides, and trampolines. Additionally, visitors can enjoy the bistro and participate in activities like kayaking and stand-up paddleboarding.
name: Snowtrax Alpine Activity Centre & Snowsports Shop
address: 15 Matchams Ln, Christchurch, BH23 6AW, United Kingdom

excerpt: Parking, toilets & a cafe are all available at this pebble beach with a nature reserve at one end.

It is designated as a Local Nature Reserve, Site of Scientific Interest, and Special Area of Conservation.

address: Southbourne, Bournemouth, BH6 4EW, United Kingdom

detail_description: Science Zone UK in Bournemouth is an interactive museum that offers a wide range of exhibits for families to explore and learn together. The venue also features workshops like fizzy science, a sensory room for young children, and a planetarium dome. Additionally, there's a coding program where kids can create their own video games.
